Package: metagMisc
Title: Miscellaneous functions for metagenomic analysis
Version: 0.0.2
Authors@R: person("Vladimir", "Mikryukov", email = "vmikryukov@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: metagMisc package contains miscellaneous functions for metagenomic analysis, including data transformations, several parsers (for USERCH UC-format; BLAST, SINA and STAMPA outputs, etc.), taxonomy handlers (SILVA, AMPTk), phyloseq-shortcuts (multiple rarefaction, phyloseq splitting and exporting), and DADA2-shortcuts (error rate estimation on the subset of data, export of denoised amplicons in fasta).
Depends: R (>= 3.3.1)
Imports:
    plyr (>= 1.8.0),
    phyloseq (>= 1.19.0),
    DESeq2 (>= 1.14.0),
    dada2 (>= 1.3.3),
    vegan (>= 2.4-0),
    ggplot2 (>= 2.2.0),
    openssl (>= 0.9.6)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
